official_title: To authorize the minting of coins to commemorate the 1995 Special Olympics World Games.
short_title: 1995 Special Olympics World Games Commemorative Coin Act

summary.text: 1995 Special Olympics World Games Commemorative Coin Act - Directs the Secretary of the Treasury to issue one-dollar silver coins emblematic of the 1995 Special Olympics World Games. Mandates that the surcharges collected from the sale of such coins be paid to the 1995 Special Olympics World Games Organizing Committee, Inc.
